headlines.description: — Miles Bridges scored 26 points and the Charlotte Hornets used a finishing 12-0 run to beat the Brooklyn Nets 105-102 on Saturday night and snap a nine-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets close with a 12-0 run to beat the Nets 105-102 and snap a nine-game losing streak

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Dillon Brooks had 27 points, Alperen Sengun and Aaron Holiday added 20 each and the Houston Rockets sailed to a 146-117 win over the New Orleans Pelicans on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brooks has 27 points to lead Houston Rockets to 146-117 win over New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Trae Young had 36 points and Caris Lavert added 26 off the bench as the Atlanta Hawks held off the Indiana Pacers 120-118 on Saturday night for their third win in four games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trae Young scores 36 points and Hawks hold off Pacers rally for 120-118 win

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole scored 34 points and the NBA-worst Washington Wizards won their second straight game, beating Toronto 118-117 on Saturday night when Raptors guard Jamal Shead’s running layup at...
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards beat Raptors 118-117 when Shead's basket at buzzer ruled late

headlines.description: — Josh Giddey scored 26 points and the Chicago Bulls rallied from a 17-point, first-half deficit to beat the Miami Heat 114-109 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giddey scores 26 to lead Bulls' comeback from 17 down to beat the Heat 114-109

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero scored 29 points, Cole Anthony added 22 and the Orlando Magic beat Milwaukee 111-109 on Saturday to end a five-game skid and snap the Bucks’ four-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic end 5-game skid with a 111-109 victory over the Bucks

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 40 points, 12 rebounds, and eight assists, and the Boston Celtics held off a late rally to beat the Los Angeles Lakers 111-101 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 40, Celtics beat Lakers 111-101 after James leaves late with groin injury

events.name: Detroit Pistons at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Draymond Green hit a go-ahead 3-pointer with 35 seconds left, then secured a loose ball moments later and converted a free throw, Stephen Curry surpassed 25,000 points and the Golden State Warriors held off the Detroit Pistons 115-110 on Saturday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Green hits go-ahead 3, Curry surpasses 25,000 points as Warriors hold off Pistons, 115-110
